scene.message:
Maki: Coming to a place like{nl}
this is a relief. It's like{nl}
being a normal high schooler{nl}
again.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: We're going to the{nl}
forest, right? I wonder what{nl}
this "key" even is.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: No use rushing.{nl}
Proceeding one step at a{nl}
time, surely, is the fastest{nl}
road in the end.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: We've got the{nl}
"Evil-Warding Mirror" now.{nl}
I'm not keen on it, but shall{nl}
we head to the subway?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: No burgers, no fries,{nl}
no chicken, no shakes? What{nl}
a bore!{waitkey}{clearbox}They've got nothing to sell,{nl}
and yet the clerk's all{nl}
high and mighty!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: I don't trust that shady{nl}
old man, but should we go{nl}
look anyway?{waitkey}For that "Evil-Warding{nl}
Mirror" or whatever.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: I never used to make{nl}
many detours before.{waitkey}This sort of thing is rather{nl}
fun, isn't it!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Let's go to the shrine.{nl}
I'm very curious what sort of{nl}
person is waiting there!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: A food shop with no{nl}
food — how do you figure that?{nl}
Nahaha!{waitkey}Damn it, now I'm hungry~{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Let's hit the shrine~{nl}
Maybe there'll be night{nl}
stalls{wait_fr:32}... Ayase wants a{nl}
candy apple.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: I don't like this.{nl}
Staying here, my body starts{nl}
to itch all over.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: We're not going to the{nl}
shrine? That Kuroori guy{nl}
wasn't lying, I'd say.{waitkey}{ret}

Clerk: Food? We've got none!{nl}
But take a rest here, and{nl}
your friend's head will clear{waitkey}{clearbox}and remember the next goal,{nl}
I guarantee it.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: Yesterday I ran{nl}
smack into a demon.{waitkey}{clearbox}It stared hard into my face,{nl}
then just walked off.{waitkey}{clearbox}It was almost as if...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
it were searching for someone.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: You all seem{nl}
somehow different from us.{nl}
I can't quite put it into{nl}
words, but...{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: You're a really{nl}
good person. I can tell. I'm{nl}
sure your friends think so{nl}
too.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: You do quite a{nl}
lot of bad things behind the{nl}
scenes, don't you.{waitkey}Don't forget there are{nl}
people hurt because of it!{waitkey}{ret}
